  max_actions_per_hour     autonomy.max_actions_per_hour (int)
  memory_backend           memory.backend (string)
  cost_enabled             cost.enabled (bool)
  cost_daily_limit         cost.daily_limit_usd (float)
  cost_monthly_limit       cost.monthly_limit_usd (float)

EXAMPLES
  xnullclaw alice setup                  Create agent 'alice'
  xnullclaw alice start                  Always-on Telegram agent
  xnullclaw alice start --port 3001      Also expose HTTP gateway
  xnullclaw alice start --mux            Start for mux orchestration
  xnullclaw alice cli                    Interactive chat session
  xnullclaw alice cli -m "Hello"         One-shot message
  xnullclaw alice logs -f                Follow live logs
  xnullclaw bob clone alice              New agent from alice's config
  xnullclaw bob clone alice --with-data  Clone with memory/history
  xnullclaw list                         Show all agents
  xnullclaw list --json                  Show all agents as JSON
  xnullclaw running --json               Running agents with ports
  echo "hello" | xnullclaw alice send    Send message to agent
  echo "stop" | xnullclaw send-all       Broadcast to all agents
  echo "hi" | xnullclaw send-some a,b    Send to specific agents
  xnullclaw alice config get model       Read agent's model
  xnullclaw alice config set model "openai/gpt-4o"
  xnullclaw alice costs --today          Today's costs
  xnullclaw alice drain                  Get buffered output
  xnullclaw alice watch                  Stream live output
  xnullclaw mux start                    Start mux orchestrator

FILE LAYOUT
  ~/.xnullclaw/
  ├── .tmp/nullclaw/                Git clone for building image
  ├── .mux/                         Mux process data
  │   ├── mux.pid                   Mux PID file
  │   └── logs/mux.log              Mux process log
  └── <agent>/
      ├── .meta                     Metadata (managed by xnullclaw)
      ├── config.json               Nullclaw config (edit this)
      └── data/                     All agent data (persistent)
          ├── .nullclaw/            Secrets, auth, cron (auto-managed)
          └── workspace/            Memory, files (auto-managed)

DOCKER HARDENING (applied automatically)
  - Read-only root filesystem
  - All Linux capabilities dropped
  - no-new-privileges flag
  - No ports exposed by default
  - /tmp as noexec tmpfs
  - Runs as host user (no root in container)
  - Config mounted read-only

TELEGRAM
  Each agent MUST have its own Telegram bot token.
  Telegram uses outbound long-polling — no inbound ports needed.
  Create a separate bot via @BotFather for each agent.

ENVIRONMENT
  XNULLCLAW_HOME    Base directory    (default: ~/.xnullclaw)
  XNULLCLAW_IMAGE   Docker image      (default: nullclaw:latest)
  XNULLCLAW_MUX_BIN Mux binary name   (default: xnc-mux)
